---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Aside from '../../../components/Aside.astro';
import {funktorSidebar} from '../../../data/funktor-sidebar';
import {Code} from 'astro:components';
---

<DocsLayout title="Static Web Module" sidebar={funktorSidebar}
            description="Server-rendered templates, flash sessions, and web resources">

    <h1>Static Web</h1>

    <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 !mt-2 !mb-8">
        Server-rendered HTML templates, flash sessions, web resources with cache busting,
        and Semantic UI integration.
    </p>

    <h2>Templates</h2>

    <p>Kotlinx HTML-based templates with placeholder support. Define a layout once, fill
        placeholders per page.</p>

    <Code code={`class MyTemplate : SimpleTemplateBase() {
    val content = placeholder<FlowContent>()

    override fun FlowContent.apply() {
        head { /* styles, scripts */ }
        body {
            div("ui container") {
                insert(content)
            }
        }
    }
}`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>Virtual host routing</h2>

    <p>Serve different apps on different subdomains from the same server. Each host gets its
        own Kontainer scope, routes, and static assets.</p>

    <Code code={`routing {
    // API on api.*
    host("api.*".toRegex()) {
        installApiKontainer(app, config.api.insights)
        init.get(ApiApp::class).apply { mountApiAppModule() }
    }

    // Admin panel on admin.*
    host("admin.*".toRegex()) {
        installWwwKontainer(app, config.api.insights)
        staticResources(remotePath = "assets", basePackage = "assets")

        init.use(InsightsGui::class) { mount() }
    }
}`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>Flash sessions</h2>

    <p>One-time messages that survive a redirect. Set a message, redirect, and the message
        appears on the next page load then disappears.</p>

    <Code code={`// Set a flash message before redirecting
call.flashSession.success("User created successfully")
call.flashSession.warning("Email not verified")

// On the next page, pull messages (clears them)
val messages = call.flashSession.pull()`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>Web resources</h2>

    <p>Manage CSS and JavaScript bundles with automatic cache busting via content hashing.
        Subresource integrity (SRI) hashes are computed automatically. Reference resources
        in templates and the correct versioned URL is generated.</p>

    <Aside>Cache busting means browsers always fetch the latest version after a deploy,
        while caching indefinitely otherwise. No more "clear your cache" instructions.
    </Aside>

    <h2>PrismJS integration</h2>

    <p>Built-in support for PrismJS syntax highlighting in server-rendered pages.
        Useful for documentation sites or admin panels that display code.</p>

    <div class="mt-12">
        <a href="/ultra/funktor/testing"
           class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg bg-brand-400/10 text-brand-400 border border-brand-400/30 hover:bg-brand-400/20 transition-all font-medium">
            Testing Module &rarr;
        </a>
    </div>

</DocsLayout>
